SRP158491.description: We collected and compared samples from the cohort consisted of six groups as follows: methotrexate (MTX) monotherapy, combination therapy of MTX and infliximab (IFX), tocilizumab (TCZ) monotherapy, age- and gender-matched HC, and a small number of synovial fluid samples. In order to reduce variation due to the proportion of cells at each developmental stage, we performed transcriptome analysis after sorting CD4+ and CD8+ T cells according to developmental stage. We created a gene list that was significantly expressed in RA T cells, and revealed that pathways such as mTORC1, IL-2-stat5, Cell cycle and interferon-related genes were significantly enriched among them. Overall design: Examination among healthy controls and patients with rheumatoid arthritis, including before and after treatment
SRP158491.protocol_description: Total RNA from were extracted using RNeasy Micro kit (Qiagen). 0.2 or 1 ng of total RNA from each dose and biological replicate were reverse transcribed to cDNA with SuperScript® VILO™ cDNA Synthesis Kit. Then cDNA is amplified using Ion AmpliSeq™ technology. After primer digestion, adapters and molecular barcodes were ligated to the amplicons followed by magnetic bead purification. Libraries were then diluted to 75 pM and pooled equally, with eighteen individual samples per pool.
SRP158491.publication_title: Multi-dimensional analysis identified rheumatoid arthritis-driving pathway in human T cell.
SRP158491.title: Gene expressions of T cells in each developmental stages in healthy volunteers and patients with rheumatoid arthritis
